column61: Departing station 93/26.7  Sarting with inshore stations.
Heading south back to line 93.  This is an off effort transit. Heading=168 degrees.
Fish caught by crew member off stern.  Stopping so he can reel it in.
Heading change to 343 degrees, around the coast guard cutter.
Stopped under NAVY orders, live fire exercise.
Slowing down to 8 knots, oceanographers want to reach next station at 7:30 and we are ahead of schedule.

column62: speed less than 3 knots for net tow."
